description:
## Severity
Major
## Dimension
security
## Location
src/plugins/manager.rs:714-783, src/plugins/manager.rs:619-628
## Violation
install_from_marketplace's PluginSourceDef::Url arm correctly refuses to clone when git_ref is None (preventing silent HEAD-tracking) — but install_from_git accepts `git_ref: Option<&str>` and passes it straight to git_clone without that guard. Quoted lines:

    // install_from_marketplace — guarded:
    if git_ref.is_none() {
        return Err(PluginError::InvalidManifest(format!(
            "Plugin source URL '{url}' has no `ref`; \
             refusing to track upstream HEAD..."
        )));
    }
    ...
    // install_from_git — UNguarded:
    pub fn install_from_git(
        &mut self,
        url: &str,
        git_ref: Option<&str>,
    ) -> Result<String, PluginError> {
        ...
        let commit_sha = git_clone(url, &dest, git_ref)?;

`/plugin install <git-url>` from the REPL (slash.rs:1201-1206) calls install_from_git with `None`, meaning the user CLI path silently tracks upstream HEAD — exactly the case the marketplace path was hardened against in crosslink #249.
## Mandated refactor
Move the git_ref.is_none() guard into git_clone itself (or a higher-level helper that both installers call), with an explicit `allow_head: bool` parameter that defaults to false. Update slash.rs:1201-1206 to prompt the user for a tag/branch/SHA when bare `/plugin install <git-url>` is given, rather than passing None.
## Filed from QA review dispatch
